{
  "stem": "3964.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I believe it took me about three or four weeks to realize [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that I-- I was a free person.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Just the significance of walking on a sidewalk was difficult to comprehend [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after you have been treated like an animal and walking on the street all these years.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But eventually, I realized that I was a free man now.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] After a while, of course, I got used to the idea of being a free man.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Number one, the food I was eating indicated that I was free.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had no one beating me up, ordering me around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But of course, I had lost-- the most precious thing in my life was my family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Nobody was there anymore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But I always had hope that my sister was still alive, because the last time I'd seen her was in Stuthoff, and she was in pretty good condition yet at that time, good enough to survive.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "From the hospital, I went to a sanatorium to recuperate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I weighed in at that time at 72 pounds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Needless to say, I was skin and bones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In a period of about four months, May, June, July, August, September, I recuperated enough to be able to be on my own.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "At least I felt I could be on my own.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And since I had no family, nevertheless hoped that my sister had survived, I proceeded to go back to my hometown, Gemunden.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Big surprise I arrived there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Obviously, nobody expected me.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
